    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.111 Quota 71A/45a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State (<persName type="from"
                            >Carr</persName>) to the Rumanian Minister (<persName type="to"
                            >Davila</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-21">June 21,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I enclose three copies of the
                    President’s Proclamation No. 2048 of June 16, 1933,<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d482fn33">48 Stat. (pt. 2) 1697.</note> establishing immigration
                    quotas for the year beginning July 1, 1933.</p>
                <p>As you will observe this Proclamation omits any reference to Bessarabia. The
                    effect of this omission is to abolish the Bessarabian quota established under
                    Executive Order No. 1952 [<hi rend="italic">Proclamation No. 1953</hi>] of June
                    19, 1931.<note n="34" xml:id="d482fn34">47 Stat. (pt. 2) 2456.</note> The
                    Bessarabian quota area has been included within the Rumanian quota area and, as
                    you will note upon comparing the new order with that of June 19, 1931, the
                    Rumanian quota has been increased from 295 to 377.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
